This paper deals with modal description logics, which are a subfield of knowledge representation and reasoning. The paper discusses the expressive power of a specific logic, S5-ALC, and its embedding into a modal first-order logic. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including logic (cs.LO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DL). However, given the focus on modal logics and knowledge representation, cs.LO and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
